From: Claude (devcontainer agent)
Date: 2026-04-27
Subject: [I1] devcontainer.json: pass SMUDGE_DEVCONTAINER_BYPASS and
         SMUDGE_DEVCONTAINER_INCLUDE_HOST_GITCONFIG through remoteEnv

Why this is a separate patch
============================
This devcontainer mounts /workspace/.devcontainer as read-only inside
the container, so an agent running inside cannot edit devcontainer.json
directly. Apply this patch from the host (or any environment with write
access to .devcontainer/), then commit and push.

What this fixes (review item I1)
================================
The previous round of post_install hardening added two opt-in env vars
that the script reads:

  SMUDGE_DEVCONTAINER_BYPASS                    — gate on bypassPermissions
  SMUDGE_DEVCONTAINER_INCLUDE_HOST_GITCONFIG    — restore [include] of host gitconfig

Their docstrings tell users to "set in remoteEnv (or localEnv
pass-through)", but devcontainer.json declared neither in containerEnv
nor in remoteEnv and did not have a `${localEnv:...}` pass-through
either. Setting either variable on the host shell never reached the
script, so both opt-ins were write-only — only an editor manually
running `SMUDGE_DEVCONTAINER_BYPASS=1 uv run …` from inside the
container could flip them.

The fix adds both as `${localEnv:...:}` pass-throughs in `remoteEnv`,
matching the pattern already used for CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN and
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY. The trailing `:` in `${localEnv:VAR:}` provides an
empty-string default when the host has not set the variable, so the
existing default-off behavior in post_install is preserved.

If a future devcontainer-cli version applies remoteEnv only to user
shells (not to postCreateCommand), move these two entries to
containerEnv. Spec-compliant CLIs apply remoteEnv to the entire
process tree including lifecycle commands, so remoteEnv is the
correct first choice today.

How to apply
============
From a shell on the host (NOT inside the devcontainer):

  cd <smudge repo root>
  git apply paad/code-reviews/deferred/2026-04-27-devcontainer-remoteenv-passthroughs.patch
  git add .devcontainer/devcontainer.json
  git commit -m "fix(devcontainer): pass SMUDGE_DEVCONTAINER_* opt-in flags through remoteEnv (I1)"

Then push.

---
--- a/.devcontainer/devcontainer.json
+++ b/.devcontainer/devcontainer.json
@@ -67,7 +67,9 @@
   },
   "remoteEnv": {
     "CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN": "${localEnv:CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN:}",
-    "ANTHROPIC_API_KEY": "${localEnv:ANTHROPIC_API_KEY:}"
+    "ANTHROPIC_API_KEY": "${localEnv:ANTHROPIC_API_KEY:}",
+    "SMUDGE_DEVCONTAINER_BYPASS": "${localEnv:SMUDGE_DEVCONTAINER_BYPASS:}",
+    "SMUDGE_DEVCONTAINER_INCLUDE_HOST_GITCONFIG": "${localEnv:SMUDGE_DEVCONTAINER_INCLUDE_HOST_GITCONFIG:}"
   },
   "initializeCommand": "test -f \"$HOME/.gitconfig\" || touch \"$HOME/.gitconfig\"",
   "workspaceMount": "source=${localWorkspaceFolder},target=/workspace,type=bind,consistency=delegated",
